<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kimberly is a senior undergraduate Mathematics and Chemistry double major at Williams College, and she will be attending graduate school in Fall 2021 to pursue a Ph.D. in Mathematics. She aspires to work as a mathematician, increasing representation for other black women in mathematics and sharing the beauty and fun associated with the field. Besides mathematics, Kimberly has a passion for all kinds of art: bullet journaling, quilting, watercolor painting, and more.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_1837" style="width: 125px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1837" data-attachment-id="1837" data-permalink="https://blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/2021/02/08/building-an-online-academic-profile-begins-with-your-website/peter_headshot/" data-orig-file="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?fit=466%2C462&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="466,462" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Peter_headshot" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?fit=300%2C297&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?fit=466%2C462&amp;ssl=1" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-1837" src="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?resize=115%2C114" alt="" width="115" height="114" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?resize=300%2C297&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i1.wp.com/blogs.ams.org/mathmentoringnetwork/files/2021/02/Peter_headshot.png?w=466&amp;ssl=1 466w" sizes="(max-width: 115px) 100vw, 115px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-1837" class="wp-caption-text">Peter Hollander</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Peter is a senior Mathematics major at Williams College. He is also a four-year member of the Williams Crew team and an avid runner, cyclist, and rock climber. He will be attending graduate school in Fall 2021, pursuing a Ph.D. in Mathematics, his ultimate goal being to teach and research mathematics.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><br />[1] A domain name is just the main part of your website hyperlink. You might want your domain name to be your name; for example, if your name is “First M. Last,” you could make your domain name “www.firstmlast.com” so people could easily find you!</p>
